verbose_text: The late embryogenesis abundant (LEA) proteins, including LEA14, accumulate in the embryo during seed maturation and are associated with dehydration in seeds XREF_BIBR; however, AtLEA5 (also called SAG21) is constitutively expressed in roots and reproductive organs but not in seeds, and has a specific role in protection against oxidative stress XREF_BIBR.
evidence: AtLEA5 (also called SAG21) is constitutively expressed
